<notesStmt><note>Brian Keating O'Dwyer was a government scout, wagon master, teamster, and Dodge City, Kansas, saloon keeper in the 1870s. John S. Bell was director of the U. S. Secret Service from 1888-1890. Buffalo Bill's Wild West opened in Erastina, Staten Island, New York, May 30, 1886.</note></notesStmt>

